<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Belief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<div class="infobox sisterproject">
<div style="float: left;">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Wiktionary-logo-en.svg" class="image" title="Wiktionary-logo-en.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/50px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png" width="50" height="54" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
<div style="margin-left: 60px;">Look up <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/belief" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:belief">belief</a></b></i> in <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary" title="Wiktionary">Wiktionary</a>, the free dictionary.</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/belief" class="external text" title="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/belief" rel="nofollow">Belief</a> entry in the <i><a href="/wiki/Stanford_Encyclopedia_of_Philosophy" title="Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy">Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy</a></i> by Eric Schwitzgebel</li>
<li><a href="http://www.beliefnet.com/story/76/story_7665_1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.beliefnet.com/story/76/story_7665_1.html" rel="nofollow">Beliefnet</a> - Belief-o-matic</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hippylife.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=section&amp;id=14&amp;Itemid=40" class="external text" title="http://www.hippylife.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=section&amp;id=14&amp;Itemid=40" rel="nofollow">Compare Different Beliefs</a> Information on different religions/beliefs</li>
<li><a href="http://www.pariharam.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.pariharam.com/" rel="nofollow">Beliefs and Practices</a> Belief refers to a part of a wider Spirituality</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nobeliefs.com/beliefs.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.nobeliefs.com/beliefs.htm" rel="nofollow">Think without Beliefs</a> Does rational thinking require the adherence to beliefs at all?</li>
<li><a href="http://www.isgodreligious.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.isgodreligious.com/" rel="nofollow">Religious Beliefs</a> Submit a belief and read about others' thoughts.</li>
<li><a href="http://ajburger.homestead.com/ethics.html" class="external text" title="http://ajburger.homestead.com/ethics.html" rel="nofollow">Ethics of Belief</a> Classic WK Clifford essay that belief by its nature is unethical, with counterpoint by William James</li>
</ul>
